l_main_2525787\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104anj1665702794138.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/anj1665702794138.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/anj1665702794138.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"anj1665702794138\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define Structure Worksheet (Components)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Define Structure worksheet to create or edit the component data structure and set the properties of the component, and its child objects.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"anj1665702794138__p_d5447e1_d5448e1_d5449e1\">The component structure defines the component data and the way it is accessed and validated at runtime. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"djm1704694970422.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/djm1704694970422.html\" title=\"Every component has a data structure that defines its component entities and fields, and the path required to access the data. The data structure affects the validation rules for data I/O, such as enforcing referential integrity constraints.\">Component Data Structure</a>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"anj1665702794138__section_vsl_th2_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d596929e61\">Tools</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"anj1665702794138__ul_iz2_5h2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"anj1665702794138__li_d2552e1_d2553e1_d2554e1\">Resource Browser—lists templates and modeled objects\n          (entities and fields) that can be used to create component entities and fields in the\n          component structure. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"anj1665702794138__li_d2555e1_d2556e1_d2557e1\">Component Structure Editor—shows the objects in the\n          component structure, and selected properties, as a tree. You can edit these properties\n          here or in the Properties Inspector. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"anj1665702794138__li_d2558e1_d2559e1_d2560e1\">Properties Inspector—shows the properties of the object\n          selected in the Component Structure Editor, and enables you to edit them. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"anj1665702794138__section_lmm_5h2_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d596929e79\">How to</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"anj1665702794138__ul_k5v_vh2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"anj1665702794138__li_d2561e1_d2562e1_d2563e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zii1704964501123.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zii1704964501123.html\" title=\"For services and server pages, use the Define Structure worksheet to add and organize entities and fields in the component structure.\">Define the Component Structure</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"anj1665702794138__li_d2564e1_d2565e1_d2566e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yed1704964703330.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yed1704964703330.html\" title=\"The number of objects available for selection in the Resource Browser may be very large, so you can filter the content in a variety of ways, depending on context.\">Filter and Search for Objects in Resource Browser</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"anj1665702794138__ul_m5v_vh2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"anj1665702794138__li_d2567e1_d2568e1_d2569e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qle1665702773192.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qle1665702773192.html\" title=\"Use the Uniface IDE to develop an application, following the Uniface development paradigm of Model, Construct, Build, and Deploy.\">Using the Uniface IDE</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"anj1665702794138__li_d2570e1_d2571e1_d2572e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dkp1665702773261.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkp1665702773261.html\" title=\"Although development objects can be quite different in content and purpose, the way you create, edit and delete them in the Uniface IDE is essentially the same.\">Working with Development Objects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/djm1704694970422.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Component Data Structure</a><p>Every component has a data structure that defines its component entities and fields, and the path required to access the data. The data structure affects the validation rules for data I/O, such as enforcing referential integrity constraints.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525787\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525787\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define Structure Worksheet (Components) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define Structure Worksheet (Components) Use the Define Structure worksheet to create or edit the component data structure and set the properties of the component, and its child objects. The component structure defines the component data and the way it is accessed and validated at runtime. For more information, see Component Data Structure . Tools Resource Browser—lists templates and modeled objects (entities and fields) that can be used to create component entities and fields in the component structure. Component Structure Editor—shows the objects in the component structure, and selected properties, as a tree. You can edit these properties here or in the Properties Inspector. Properties Inspector—shows the properties of the object selected in the Component Structure Editor, and enables you to edit them. How to Define the Component Structure Filter and Search for Objects in Resource Browser Using the Uniface IDE Working with Development Objects Related Links Component Data Structure Every component has a data structure that defines its component entities and fields, and the path required to access the data. The data structure affects the validation rules for data I/O, such as enforcing referential integrity constraints. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}